ncenter\" title=\"ebook-banner\" alt=\" \" src=\"http://income.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Community_banner.png\" width=\"468\" height=\"60\" /></a></p><p style=\"text-align: center\"><a href=\"http://www.mylanderpages.com/income/howtocreateawebsiteebook_4\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-577\" title=\"ebook-banner\" alt=\" \" src=\"http://income.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/howtocreateawebsiteebook1.png\" width=\"641\" height=\"123\" /></a></p><p>The post <a href=\"http://income.com/1934/grow-your-small-business-by-exporting/\">Grow Your Small Business By Exporting</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://income.com\">income.com</a>.</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/income/YOKa/~4/pdViAvltCp0\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>") (wfw:commentRss nil "http://income.com/1934/grow-your-small-business-by-exporting/feed/") (slash:comments nil "0") (feedburner:origLink nil "http://income.com/1934/grow-your-small-business-by-exporting/"))) ("3 Ideas For Starting A Small Business In The Pet Niche" "<div id=\"attachment_1929\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\" style=\"width: 285px\"><a href=\"http://income.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/x_0_0_0_14084666_300.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1929\" alt=\"There's money to be made in starting a small business that fills a need for pet goods and services.\" src=\"http://income.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/x_0_0_0_14084666_300.jpg\" width=\"275\" height=\"300\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">There’s money to be made in starting a small business that fills a need for pet goods and services.</p></div><p>Pets are as much part of the family as grandma is for many households.</p><p>They have their own beds, their own bathrooms, food, toys, accessories, sometimes they even eat at the table. Our four-legged furry friends – although sometimes they be scaly or lacking in the leg department, instead sporting fins and feathers – are so much part of daily life that they’ve more or less become indirect consumers of a burgeoning pet goods and services industry.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.income.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Income.com</a> wants you to know that using pigs to sniff out valuable truffles isn’t the only way you can profit off animals. More than ever, families are spending money on their pets for a variety of reasons: Halloween costumes, boarding and doggie hotels, grooming, training, specialty foods and more.</p><p>Cat cash and dog dollars may not be real things, but they might as well be. Pet owners are shelling out for their pets, and there’s no indication the fascination with providing world-class amenities for an animal that licks its own butt to stay clean is ending anytime soon. So if you’re trying to come up with ideas for starting a small business but nothing is coming to mind, <a href=\"http://income.com/67/3-keys-for-starting-a-successful-small-business/\" target=\"_blank\">look no further than a startup in the lucrative pet goods and services industry</a>.</p><h2><strong>Get Those Pooches In Line</strong></h2><p>Ever had trouble with Fido rooting through the garbage bin night after night or chewing entire holes in drywall? Then you know that even man’s best friend can get on his last nerve every so often.</p><p>Dogs are born guardians, but they often need some education in order to realize their potential. Here’s where your <span style=\"text-decoration: line-through\">animal</span> entrepreneurial instincts kick in: owners need well-behaving dogs, dogs need training, but owners can’t or won’t do it. Right there is your chance to turn your life-long appreciation of animals into a business opportunity. Heck, Cesar Milan even turned it into a TV show!</p><p>First, you’ll need to get some real-world experience in dog training and <a href=\"http://education-portal.com/articles/How_to_Become_a_Dog_Obedience_Trainer_Step-by-Step_Career_Guide.html\" target=\"_blank\">get certified</a>. There’s a number of obedience training programs that churn out accredited dog trainers. Then find customers. Why not try posting flyers in a local dog park and using word-of-mouth marketing through friends and family? To boost the customer experience, you can even print out inexpensive diplomas for dog owners to keep.</p><h2><strong>“Waiter, I want my food right meow!”</strong></h2><p>Some pets are as picky about the food they eat as the toddlers they sometimes act like. Cats are notorious food snobs and owners will go out of their way to find soft food made of turkey giblets when tuna, chicken or beef just simply won’t do.</p><p><a href=\"http://income.com/20/how-to-know-somebody-was-born-to-be-an-entrepreneur/\" target=\"_blank\">If you’ve got a passion</a> for cooking and experimenting with new recipes, becoming a specialty chef for pet foods may be an opportunity you want to explore. You can market your products as exclusive or even work on a case-by-case basis and charge a premium fee for personalized services. Fancy Feast has got nothing on you. <a href=\"http://smallbusiness.chron.com/start-pet-treat-business-4409.html\" target=\"_blank\">Another potential avenue for money-making is pet treats</a>, which are a frequent buy for owners that want to keep their pets happy.</p><p>Just remember that nutrition is the overarching focus when making pet foods. Whether you want to create a protein-rich food to market to sporting dog owners or an all-around healthy entree to keep cats lean and mean – emphasis on the latter – there are a number of different products to create. Packaging is also a crucial element. People eat foods that look good, and before that, they choose foods with the most aesthetically pleasing packaging. There’s ample opportunity to create color-popping labels that attract attention, and ultimately, business.</p><h2><strong>All Dogs Go To Heaven</strong></h2><p>Unfortunately, like all things we love, cherish and share memories of, we meet a harsh reality when pets die. But there’s a better way to burying the dead in a mass grave and encountering a Pet Semetary-like experience.</p><p>Cremating pets is a trending business venture and operators are finding that pet owners are willing to pay top money for services.</p><p>“When people come to the funeral home and I tell them how much it is to cremate their grandfather, it’s never cheap enough for them,” Bob Walczyk, owner of a Green Bay pet crematorium, <a href=\"http://www.businessweek.com/articles/2012-09-07/theres-never-been-a-better-time-to-be-a-dead-pet#p1\" target=\"_blank\">told Bloomberg Businessweek</a>. “They’ll say, ‘How much? You’ve got to be kidding me!’ But when the exact same family brings their dog next door, they don’t even ask about money. They just tell me what they want and they take out their checkbook.”</p><p>There’s also an opportunity to resonate on an emotional level with patrons. You can repurpose ashes into a ceramic decoration of sorts that includes an imprint of the pet’s paw that owners will certainly appreciate as a memento.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.income.com/\">Income.com</a> knows brainstorming ideas for starting a small business can be difficult, but sometimes you need look no farther than the ball of fur cuddled around your ankles. Owners are increasingly spending big money for pet products and services, and you can make money from that by starting up a business that caters to such needs. Be it obedience training, food preparation or crematory services, pet small businesses are worth investigating.</p><p><a href=\"http://income.com/forum/forum.php\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" title=\"ebook-banner\" alt=\" \" src=\"http://income.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Community_banner.png\" width=\"468\" height=\"60\" /></a></p><p style=\"text-align: center\"><a href=\"http://www.mylanderpages.com/income/howtocreateawebsiteebook_4\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-577\" title=\"ebook-banner\" alt=\" \" src=\"http://income.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/howtocreateawebsiteebook1.png\" width=\"641\" height=\"123\" /></a></p><p>The post <a href=\"http://income.com/1928/3-ideas-for-starting-a-small-business-in-the-pet-niche/\">3 Ideas For Starting A Small Business In The Pet Niche</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://income.com\">income.com</a>.</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/income/YOKa/~4/oGljsEcFe_Q\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>" "http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/income/YOKa/~3/oGljsEcFe_Q/" (20808 30169) new 4 nil nil ((title nil "3 Ideas For Starting A Small Business In The Pet Niche") (link nil "http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/income/YOKa/~3/oGljsEcFe_Q/") (comments nil "http://income.com/1928/3-ideas-for-starting-a-small-business-in-the-pet-niche/#comments") (pubDate nil "Tue, 19 Mar 2013 14:27:37 +0000") (dc:creator nil "Tedd Johnson") (category nil "Articles") (category nil "Ideas For Starting A Small Business") (category nil "Small Business") (category nil "Featured") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "http://income.com/?p=1928") (description nil "<p>Pets are as much part of the family as grandma is for many households. They have their own beds, their own bathrooms, food, toys, accessories, sometimes they even eat at the table. Our four-legged furry friends &#8211; although sometimes they be scaly or lacking in the leg department, instead sporting fins and feathers &#8211; are [...]</p><p>The post <a href=\"http://income.com/1928/3-ideas-for-starting-a-small-business-in-the-pet-niche/\">3 Ideas For Starting A Small Business In The Pet Niche</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://income.com\">income.com</a>.</p>") (content:encoded nil "<div id=\"attachment_1929\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\" style=\"width: 285px\"><a href=\"http://income.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/x_0_0_0_14084666_300.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1929\" alt=\"There's money to be made in starting a small business that fills a need for pet goods and services.\" src=\"http://income.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/x_0_0_0_14084666_300.jpg\" width=\"275\" height=\"300\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">There&#8217;s money to be made in starting a small business that fills a need for pet goods and services.</p></div><p>Pets are as much part of the family as grandma is for many households.</p><p>They have their own beds, their own bathrooms, food, toys, accessories, sometimes they even eat at the table. Our four-legged furry friends &#8211; although sometimes they be scaly or lacking in the leg department, instead sporting fins and feathers &#8211; are so much part of daily life that they&#8217;ve more or less become indirect consumers of a burgeoning pet goods and services industry.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.income.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Income.com</a> wants you to know that using pigs to sniff out valuable truffles isn&#8217;t the only way you can profit off animals. More than ever, families are spending money on their pets for a variety of reasons: Halloween costumes, boarding and doggie hotels, grooming, training, specialty foods and more.</p><p>Cat cash and dog dollars may not be real things, but they might as well be. Pet owners are shelling out for their pets, and there&#8217;s no indication the fascination with providing world-class amenities for an animal that licks its own butt to stay clean is ending anytime soon. So if you&#8217;re trying to come up with ideas for starting a small business but nothing is coming to mind, <a href=\"http://income.com/67/3-keys-for-starting-a-successful-small-business/\" target=\"_blank\">look no further than a startup in the lucrative pet goods and services industry</a>.</p><h2><strong>Get Those Pooches In Line</strong></h2><p>Ever had trouble with Fido rooting through the garbage bin night after night or chewing entire holes in drywall? Then you know that even man&#8217;s best friend can get on his last nerve every so often.</p><p>Dogs are born guardians, but they often need some education in order to realize their potential. Here&#8217;s where your <span style=\"text-decoration: line-th