ng-a-successful-small-business/\" target=\"_blank\">relished the joys of success</a>, suffered the blows of defeat and more often than not, come away with valuable life skills, business intelligence and first-hand experience of examples of entrepreneurship.</p><p>Knowledge is power, and <a href=\"http://income.com/\">Income.com</a> also knows that knowledge is money. Have a steel-trap of a mind that’s chock full with inventive and innovative business ideas? Don’t know how to parlay that intellectual richness into real world riches? There’s a simple answer to that dilemma: <a href=\"http://smallbusiness.foxbusiness.com/starting-a-business/2011/11/03/five-tips-on-how-to-start-consulting-business/\" target=\"_blank\">Start a small-business consulting service</a>.</p><p>There are scores of aspiring entrepreneurs out there just like you, only some don’t possess the know-how or ingenuity that accomplished small-business owners build up through their careers.</p><p>Time to put that knowledge to use and earn some good money while you’re at it. You’re going to need to pin down your specialty area, network to create a list of contacts and develop a powerhouse online presence.</p><h2><strong>Choose your consulting discipline</strong></h2><p>The best thing about being an entrepreneur is you’re involved in just about every aspect of business operations. As such, you start to develop an expertise in a number of fields that you can then translate into consulting knowledge.</p><p>There are any number of services an entrepreneur will seek advice from consultants on: accounting, auditing, marketing, sales, increasing revenue, taxes, talent management, expansion, communications, technology, general counseling, mentorship.</p><h2><strong>Network, network and network some more</strong></h2><p>The key to becoming a successful consultant lies in the ability for you to tap an unending list of clients. Rolodexes may have fallen by the wayside, but the notion of having a database of contacts to crawl is still supremely important to consulting.</p><p>Reach out to people you’ve been in business with before: firms you’ve collaborated with, suppliers, even competitors. <a href=\"http://income.com/90/social-media-a-proven-marketing-initiative-for-entrepreneurs/\" target=\"_blank\">Social media is also key</a>, it’s the 21st century forum for business networking. Create a LinkedIn profile and expand from there. Establishing and nurturing business relationships is crucial, entrepreneurs will look to you as a partner and confidant and you need to be prepared for that.</p><h2><strong>Online or bust</strong></h2><p><a href=\"http://income.com/the-small-business-internet-startup-tutorial/\" target=\"_blank\">Build a small-business website</a> for your consulting service as soon as you can. Contrary to other common small-business uses, your website won’t really serve an ecommerce function, but will still act as a central hub to your operations.</p><p>Have an in-house platform for online communication so prospective clients can easily reach you. Make sure to incorporate your social media accounts, as well. Another important element is testimonials. After working with businesses, solicit them to provide a reference or testimonial. Many will often be glad to help you as you helped them.</p><p><a href=\"http://income.com/\">Income.com</a> knows you can put those entrepreneurial skills to use, it’s only a matter of finding your consulting niche. Identify what you’re good at, stress the value you can provide, network like never before and make sure your online presence boosts your consultancy profile.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"http://income.com/forum/forum.php\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" title=\"ebook-banner\" alt=\" \" src=\"http://income.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Community_banner.png\" width=\"468\" height=\"60\" /></a></p><p style=\"text-align: center\"><a href=\"http://www.mylanderpages.com/income/howtocreateawebsiteebook_4\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-577\" title=\"ebook-banner\" alt=\" \" src=\"http://income.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/howtocreateawebsiteebook1.png\" width=\"641\" height=\"123\" /></a></p><p>The post <a href=\"http://income.com/1892/how-to-start-a-consulting-business/\">How To Start A Consulting Business</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://income.com\">income.com</a>.</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/income/YOKa/~4/HF7pCO1RAH8\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>" "http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/income/YOKa/~3/HF7pCO1RAH8/" (20796 51014) new 8 nil nil ((title nil "How To Start A Consulting Business") (link nil "http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/income/YOKa/~3/HF7pCO1RAH8/") (comments nil "http://income.com/1892/how-to-start-a-consulting-business/#comments") (pubDate nil "Sun, 10 Mar 2013 17:47:50 +0000") (dc:creator nil "Tedd Johnson") (category nil "Articles") (category nil "Ideas For Starting A Small Business") (category nil "Small Business") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "http://income.com/?p=1892") (description nil "<p>Entrepreneurs know the ins and outs of their businesses pretty well. They&#8217;ve been around the block a couple times, relished the joys of success, suffered the blows of defeat and more often than not, come away with valuable life skills, business intelligence and first-hand experience of examples of entrepreneurship. Knowledge is power, and Income.com also knows that knowledge [...]</p><p>The post <a href=\"http://income.com/1892/how-to-start-a-consulting-business/\">How To Start A Consulting Business</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://income.com\">income.com</a>.</p>") (content:encoded nil "<div id=\"attachment_1893\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\" style=\"width: 310px\"><a href=\"http://income.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/x_0_0_0_14070071_300.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1893\" alt=\"Use your examples of entrepreneurship as models for others in a consultancy small business.\" src=\"http://income.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/x_0_0_0_