 scrounging for ideas for starting a small business and your brainstorm turns out to be little more than a braindrizzle, look no further than the front yard, because landscaping businesses are never out of season.</p><p><a href=\"http://income.com/\">Income.com</a> knows hungry entrepreneurs are always looking for the next big thing, but in that pursuit, they sometimes lose sight of the proven money-making enterprises, like lawn care.</p><p>Raking the leaves is the last thing a homeowner wants to do on a Sunday afternoon, and you can take advantage of that potential to sell a service by <a href=\"http://smallbusiness.chron.com/ways-start-own-landscaping-company-2417.html\" target=\"_blank\">starting your own lawn​ care small business</a>. First you’ll have to decide which kind of landscaping business you want to start, then, you’ll need to spread the word and arm your business and employees with the right equipment.</p><h2><strong>Several options to choose from</strong></h2><p>Landscaping seems like a pretty straightforward category of business, but there’s a lot room for innovation below the surface. Not every startup has to be the standard, mow-your-lawn and rake-your-leaves style of operation.</p><p>There’s a variety of different options when considering which avenue to take. You can start a sod installation and hydroseeding firm, or you could go the weeding and pest control route. Tree care and maintenance is always a good option, as are specialty lawn care contracting opportunities. Hell, you can even mirror Eddie Scissorhands and start your own topiary small business.</p><p>It’s important to keep in mind what local competition your business would have and what the consumer demand is. If you’re in a community that’s active in gardening but lacking in its lawn fertilizer treatments, that’ll clue you in on the next path of action.</p><h2><strong>It’s not a child’s game</strong></h2><p>While any 11-year-old can mow the lawn, that kind of quality and work ethic won’t fly with clients expecting professional services. You and any employees you might have will need to brush up on the best practices for lawn trimming, thorn bush pruning and even leaf raking.</p><p>Once you feel you’ve mastered the art, apply for local certification so you can assure potential customers that you’re the real deal.</p><h2><strong>Canvas the area</strong></h2><p>To start, you’ll need to build up a local following before you can expand to outlying areas. Make some flyers and take a ride around town looking for homes with seemingly unkempt lawns and yards, they’ll be your perfect clients to start with.</p><p><a href=\"http://income.com/90/social-media-a-proven-marketing-initiative-for-entrepreneurs/\" target=\"_blank\">Get active on social media as well</a>. Images are becoming increasingly important to social connection, and what better image to post or pin than a scenic, pastoral snapshot of some of your best work.</p><h2><strong>Write off equipment</strong></h2><p>Landscaping businesses require a lot of equipment: lawn mowers, rakes, shears, gloves, protective eyewear, transportation. But don’t fret, you can write off big equipment purchases like mowers and trucks under the Section 179 deduction, which under the current parameters, allows for up to $500,000 in deductions on no more than $2 million in purchases for 2013.</p><p><a href=\"http://income.com/\">Income.com</a> knows successful <a href=\"http://income.com/67/3-keys-for-starting-a-successful-small-business/\" target=\"_blank\">entrepreneurs are all about the green</a> - in this case, both in reference to grass and money. <a href=\"http://www.nfib.com/business-resources/business-resources-item?cmsid=61783\" target=\"_blank\">Landscaping small businesses</a> are an evergreen option for making money and you can certainly hedge your bets that a lawn care startup will pay off. Know which specific kind of business you want to start, get in enough practice, identify potential clients and write off your big equipment expenses.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"http://income.com/forum/forum.php\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" title=\"ebook-banner\" alt=\" \" src=\"http://income.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Community_banner.png\" width=\"468\" height=\"60\" /></a></p><p style=\"text-align: center\"><a href=\"http://www.mylanderpages.com/income/howtocreateawebsiteebook_4\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-577\" title=\"ebook-banner\" alt=\" \" src=\"http://income.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/howtocreateawebsiteebook1.png\" width=\"641\" height=\"123\" /></a></p><p>The post <a href=\"http://income.com/1887/green-ideas-for-starting-a-small-business-landscaping/\">Green Ideas For Starting a Small Business: Landscaping</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://income.com\">income.com</a>.</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/income/YOKa/~4/uqaKrZtJX2w\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>" "http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/income/YOKa/~3/uqaKrZtJX2w/" (20795 25697) new 9 nil nil ((title nil "Green Ideas For Starting a Small Business: Landscaping") (link nil "http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/income/YOKa/~3/uqaKrZtJX2w/") (comments nil "http://income.com/1887/green-ideas-for-starting-a-small-business-landscaping/#comments") (pubDate nil "Sat, 09 Mar 2013 16:33:37 +0000") (dc:creator nil "Tedd Johnson") (category nil "Articles") (category nil "Ideas For Starting A Small Business") (category nil "Small Business") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "http://income.com/?p=1887") (description nil "<p>The old saying goes the grass is always greener on the other side. That axiom implies someone else&#8217;s grass ain&#8217;t looking too healthy, and it probably wouldn&#8217;t be out of the question for them to pay somebody to come spruce up their lawn. In that case, if you&#8217;re scrounging for ideas for starting a small [...]</p><p>The post <a href=\"http://income.com/1887/green-ideas-for-starting-a-small-business-landscaping/\">Green Ideas For Starting a Small Business: Landscaping</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://income.com\">income.com</a>.</p>") (content:encoded nil "<div id=\"attachment_1888\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\" style=\"width: 309px\"><a href=\"http://income.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/x_0_0_0_14035490_300.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1888\" alt=\"Be it hydroseeding or tree care, landscaping startups are always a great option for entrepreneurs.  \" src=\"http://income.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/x_0_0_0_14035490_300.jpg\" width=\"299\" height=\"200\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Be it hydroseeding or tree care, landscaping startups are always a great option for entrepreneurs.</p></div><p>The old saying goes the grass is always greener on the other side.</p><p>That axiom implies someone else&#8217;s grass ain&#8217;t looking too healthy, and it probably wouldn&#8217;t be out of the question for them to pay somebody to come spruce up their lawn.</p><p>In that case, if you&#8217;re scrounging for ideas for starting a small business and your brainstorm turns out to be little more than a braindrizzle, look no further than the front yard, because landscaping businesses are never out of season.</p><p><a href=\"http://income.com/\">Income.com</a> knows hungry entrepreneurs are always looking for the next big thing, but in that pursuit, they sometimes lose sight of the proven money-making enterprises, like lawn care.</p><p>Raking the leaves is the last thing a homeowner wants to do on a Sunday afternoon, and you can take advantage of that potential to sell a service by <a href=\"http://smallbusiness.chron.com/ways-start-own-landscaping-company-2417.html\" target=\"_blank\">starting your own lawn​ care small business</a>. First you&#8217;ll have to decide which kind of landscaping business you want to start, then, you&#8217;ll need to spread the word and arm your business and employees with the right equipment.</p><h2><strong>Several options to choose from</strong></h2><p>Landscaping seems like a pretty 