e.com/1887/green-ideas-for-starting-a-small-business-landscaping/feed/") (slash:comments nil "0") (feedburner:origLink nil "http://income.com/1887/green-ideas-for-starting-a-small-business-landscaping/"))) ("Small-Business Marketing Help: How To – And How Not To – Run A PPC Campaign" "<div id=\"attachment_1885\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\" style=\"width: 310px\"><a href=\"http://income.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/x_0_0_0_14074811_300.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1885\" alt=\"PPC campaigns are successful for those that know how to run them.\" src=\"http://income.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/x_0_0_0_14074811_300.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">PPC campaigns are successful for those that know how to run them.</p></div><p>Internet marketing has become a priority for small-business owners everywhere.</p><p>Much like phone calls and snail mail have fallen prey to text messaging and email, cold calling and direct mail have been replaced by online marketing methods.</p><p>However, <a href=\"http://income.com/\">Income.com</a> wants aspiring, <a href=\"http://income.com/the-small-business-internet-startup-tutorial/\" target=\"_blank\">tech-savvy entrepreneurs</a> to keep in mind digital marketing doesn’t begin and end with social media and email blasts. <a href=\"http://income.com/1806/small-business-marketing-help-for-seo-in-2013-local-search-or-bust/\" target=\"_blank\">SEO entails a lot of factors</a>, and boosting your internet presence using targeted ads is a growing trend among small enterprises.</p><p>Pay per click initiatives – PPC campaigns as they’re known - <a href=\"http://searchenginewatch.com/article/2141107/3-Ways-Local-Small-Businesses-Can-Use-PPC\" target=\"_blank\">is a technique that places a small business’s ads on a search engine</a> like Google that firms only pay for when users click on their ad to become a conversion.</p><p>The central theme to PPC is targeting and cost-efficiency. So to make sure your PPC campaign is successful, there are a couple things to keep in mind like making sure you have custom landing pages and not having enough of a specific focus in your ads.</p><h2><strong>Do not depend on Google</strong></h2><p>Using Google AdWords is the simplest way to running a PPC campaign for small-business owners unfamiliar to the channel. However, be aware that there are alternatives to Google, which may not prove to be the most effective platform for some owners. Consider breaking the Google chain and investigate using Yahoo, Bing or Amazon.</p><p>Sometimes big-name players just don’t fit your needs. In that case, consider smaller platforms like Clicksor or Chikita that provide the same services but are more attune to small-business needs.</p><h2><strong>Do have custom landing pages</strong></h2><p><a href=\"http://www.startupnation.com/business-articles/9857/1/cardinal-sin-of-ppc-advertising.htm\" target=\"_blank\">No PPC campaign is complete without custom landing pages</a>. The key to meaningful conversions is sending clickers to targeted pages that relate to the ad they clicked on. Users that are sent to home pages, shopping carts and online registration forms are unlikely to be happy with their experience and end up costing you money.</p><p>A custom landing page is a page specifically designed to work with your PPC campaign. It has to connect with what the ad purports; if you’re advertising about children’s toys, your landing page better direct the user to a specific product’s page, and not your “About Us.”</p><p>Landing pages should have distinct calls to action, a clean layout and testimonials that lend credence to your offering.</p><h2><strong>Do not ignore geographic targeting</strong></h2><p>The main draw of internet marketing is the ability for small-business owners to hyperlocalize or target their advertising efforts to reach and resonate with local customers. Optimizing for keywords that relate directly to your geographic location and that of your consumer base is hugely important to a successful PPC campaign.</p><p><a href=\"http://income.com/\">Income.com</a> knows entrepreneurs are turning to online marketing methods in droves because of the expanded reach and cost savings that are afforded to them. However, it urges entrepreneurs to not dive straight into PPC <a href=\"http://smallbusiness.yahoo.com/advisor/run-ppc-campaign-120009351.html\" target=\"_blank\">without a basic understanding</a> of the right and wrong ways to run a campaign. Just remember, there are alternatives to Google that can suffice. And don’t forget: Geo-targeting is a must for any campaign and custom landing pages will net you profitable conversions.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"http://income.com/forum/forum.php\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" title=\"ebook-banner\" alt=\" \" src=\"http://income.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Community_banner.png\" width=\"468\" height=\"60\" /></a></p><p style=\"text-align: center\"><a href=\"http://www.mylanderpages.com/income/howtocreateawebsiteebook_4\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-577\" title=\"ebook-banner\" alt=\" \" src=\"http://income.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/howtocreateawebsiteebook1.png\" width=\"641\" height=\"123\" /></a></p><p>The post <a href=\"http://income.com/1884/small-business-marketing-help-how-to-and-how-not-to-run-a-ppc-campaign/\">Small-Business Marketing Help: How To – And How Not To – Run A PPC Campaign</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://income.com\">income.com</a>.</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/income/YOKa/~4/oEcCJmUbtjA\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>" "http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/income/YOKa/~3/oEcCJmUbtjA/" (20794 606) new 10 nil nil ((title nil "Small-Business Marketing Help: How To – And How Not To – Run A PPC Campaign") (link nil "http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/income/YOKa/~3/oEcCJmUbtjA/") (comments nil "http://income.com/1884/small-business-marketing-help-how-to-and-how-not-to-run-a-ppc-campaign/#comments") (pubDate nil "F